A place of escape and relaxation also for sports enthusiasts, jogging, Nordic walking, or simply walking. When the weather is nice you can rent a boat and go for a trip. There is a kiosk right next to the car park, if you want to have a cold drink, a coffee, a tea or a pancake... In summer there are ice creams too.

It is perhaps the least pleasant of the 4 ponds in the Bois de Vincennes. Circular in shape, approximately 1400 meters, it surrounds 3 islands of which only the smallest is accessible. A refreshment bar adorns this western part of the lake. In the eastern part, it looks more like a small river, decorated with small waterfalls, but the numerous deciduous trees that border it make it less visible. To the west, the widest open part allows you to go boating. However, you can see and admire many birds around this lake.

This second large lake in the Bois de Vincennes is quite different from the other (Daumesnil). Very wild when in a boat you head towards the East and the Yellow Gate chalet. It even presents surprising natural obstacles (branches, crossing trunk under which you have to pass). For information: the closest access is via the D120.

Small oasis in this urban jungle. Quite well maintained given the surface area and the number of walkers/runners/cyclists who cross it. Very good spot for running, the course is large and pleasant. Small downside on the number of trash cans available.
Very pleasant walking route around the lake, many birds. Boat rental, refreshment bar and catering nearby.
Very pretty park with ducks, swans and other moorhens. Pleasant in all seasons.

Despite Google's blocking, I have nothing to add or take away from my comment which is in no way defamatory or offensive. You ask me for my opinion, I give it, and I believe I am authorized to do so since I worked at this place. Very beautiful NAPOLEON III period chalet classified MH. But where has the romantic style terrace material gone? I spent time there in the 70s/75s. Before its descent into hell due to disastrous management, it was a good class restaurant with a real cuisine menu and professional staff.  It has become a fair stand, which certainly corresponds to the current clientele. Sad times! A star for the place which is truly magnificent in all seasons.

One of the four lakes or ponds of the Bois de Vincennes (the others being those of Saint MandÃ©, Daumesnil and Gravelle). Shaped like a half-moon, it is surrounded by a circular road closed to vehicles where many runners and cyclists stroll. With an area of â€‹â€‹6 ha, it has three islands (the Isle of Porte-Jaune, the North Island, the South Island). Its name comes from the fact that this area was occupied by monks of the order of Minimes (the very small ones). Many birds live in this place: ducks, swans, moorhens, geese, Canada geese...
Charming place which offers many water activities (except swimming). Also ideal for runners - personally, this is where I calculate my VMA by going around the lake.
